    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="549"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/9736</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4848. Your 3741,<note n="2" xml:id="d549fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_436">p. 436</ref>.</note>
                    August 25. Foreign Office refers to its note of the 31st, cabled in my 4815
                    [4814], September 1 and states that bunkers have now been granted the <hi
                        rend="italic">Charlton Hall</hi> which is reported to have sailed from
                    Colombo on the 26th and the authorities in Egypt have been notified by telegraph
                    in order that, if requested, similar facilities may be assured her on arrival at
                    Suez or Port Said.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
